

GFS cluster configuration on GCP

✅ 1. Install Fence Agent for GCP

dnf install fence-agents-gce

On both cluster nodes:

dnf install -y fence-agents-gce
✅ 2. Create Service Account in GCP

You need a service account with permissions to control VM power.

Steps:
Go to **Google Cloud Platform Console
Navigate to:
IAM & Admin → Service Accounts
Create service account (example: fence-gcp-sa)
Assign role:
Compute Instance Admin (v1)

✅ 3. Attach Service Account to VMs Using Console

Attach this service account to both clus

🔹 Steps:
Go to:
Compute Engine → VM Instances
Select your VM (e.g., rocky-node1)
Click Stop
⚠️ You must stop the VM to change service account
Click Edit
Scroll to:
Identity and API access
Set:
Service Account → select your fencing service account
(example: fence-gcp-sa@project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com)
Access Scopes →
👉 Select: Allow full access to all Cloud APIs
Click Save
Start the VM again

✅ 4. Configure Required Scope
Compute Engine → VM Instances
Stop the VM
Click Edit
Under Identity and API access:
Service Account: (your fencing SA)
Access Scopes:
👉 Select Allow full access to all Cloud APIs

